gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 114, Wizards 106
gameRecap.excerpt: Cleveland defeated Washington, 114-106, to extend their win streak up to seven games, they’re 15-1 in their last 16 games. For Cleveland, Donovan Mitchell led the way with 40 points (five 3PM), eight rebounds, and five assists with Evan Mobley adding 22 points and eight rebounds. Kyle Kuzma led the way with 28 points (five 3PM) and four rebounds aided by Corey Kispert tallying 23 points (four 3PM) and seven rebounds for Washington in the losing effort. Cleveland wins and improves to 33-16 on the season, while Washington moves to 9-41 with the loss.
